Had I told you,

83
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,760
you wouldn't have approached me, right?

84
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:24,000
Who said I approached you?

85
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,080
I approached June.

86
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,760
Seen June lately?

87
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:56,800
Don't you know?

88
00:11:58,800 --> 00:11:59,600
Know what?

89
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,680
June... she left us years ago.

90
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,320
Are you joking?

91
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:20,200
It's not something to jest about.

92
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,360
Seriously,

93
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,280
I'm not joking.

94
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:29,960
June drowned during
our freshman year party.

95
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,720
It was all over the news.

96
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,280
I even went to her funeral.

97
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:02,800
Eating at a time like this?

98
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,000
Because of June's memory?

99
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,160
Still have feelings for her?

100
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:19,640
Nope.

101
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:26,520
I'm just reeling...

102
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,840
Camp: Knowing someone I cared for is gone...
Talay: It hit me hard too.

103
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:37,480
I even went to look for you at school,
thinking I'd tell you.

104
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,800
But you never did?

105
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:41,960
Didn't see the point.

106
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:46,760
What the hell do you mean?

107
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,880
You disrespect me again.

108
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,200
It’s such an important matter.

109
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,120
You should've told me.

110
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:55,960
And if I had?
what would you do?

111
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,800
You'd have stormed off to the funeral?

112
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:01,400
Maybe,

113
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,680
that would be my business, right?

114
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:09,200
So, not telling you is my business too.

115
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,160
Stop talking bullshit!

116
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:18,560
Camp, let's keep it civil.

117
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,760
Hear yourself!

118
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:26,040
You're the one talking bullshit first.

119
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:32,840
Fine!

120
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:37,640
After graduation,
were you still close with June?

121
00:15:45,040 --> 00:15:45,600
Not really.

122
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,440
So, why tell you?

123
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:54,080
Even if we weren't close,
you should've.

124
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,160
What should I have told you?

125
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:01,800
Since you weren't close
to June anymore?

126
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,000
We weren't close either.

127
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,760
But if I died,

128
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:25,640
June would've let you know.

129
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:36,840
You’re still into June, right?

130
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,360
Why ask again?

131
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:46,040
Who can't let go?
You or me?

132
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,280
Or it’s not true?

133
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:51,720
You keep asking about June.

134
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,600
Do you like her that much?

135
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,520
What the hell do you want to hear?

136
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:02,360
Yes, I still like her.

137
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:06,400
I still do like her.
Are you fuckin happy now?

138
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:07,800
Damn it!

139
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:41,120
Damn!

140
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,680
[Camp!]

141
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:57,000
[Camp!]

142
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:16,000
[Camp!]

143
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:20,760
[Camp!]

144
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:22,720
Who's there?

145
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,040
Talay, you?

146
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:29,640
Stop joking!

147
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:33,200
[Camp!]

148
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:38,320
[Camp!]

149
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:46,240
[You guys will never be together.]

150
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:07,200
Camp: Help me!
Talay: Camp!

151
