Talay: Camp!
Camp: Someone, help!

152
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:18,840
Camp!

153
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:22,200
Help!

154
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:26,880
Camp!

155
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:29,400
Camp, hold my hand!

156
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,600
Did you see June?

157
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:34,840
You saw June, didn't you?

158
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:38,360
Just like I did.

159
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:42,320
Just tell me!

160
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:45,280
June might be holding a grudge.

161
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:54,200
Why?

162
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:00,320
Against me?

163
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:02,400
What did I ever do?

164
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:06,200
It's not you.

165
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:09,120
She might hold a grudge against me.

166
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:12,040
What's the reason?

167
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:18,880
That day, when June died,

168
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:21,400
I was there.

169
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,720
You said you had something to talk about.

170
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,560
What was it?

171
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:49,480
I have feelings for you.

172
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:58,080
Is that so shocking?

173
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:07,640
Say something!

174
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:12,680
You're just a friend to me.

175
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:18,160
What do you mean?

176
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:22,920
After all our moments in school?

177
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:37,200
I'm into Camp.

178
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:44,640
Wait.

179
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:48,200
Both you and Camp were flirting with me,

180
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:50,960
and you two clashed because of me, right?

181
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:55,360
When did you start falling for him, huh?

182
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:01,080
I've always had a thing for Camp.

183
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,720
I just didn't want him to be with you.

184
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:11,720
Then why did you do this to me?

185
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:14,200
Is it funny?

186
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:17,200
I poured my heart out to you!

187
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:20,360
I’m sorry.

188
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:28,640
If there was no Camp,

189
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:31,680
would you have given me a chance?

190
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:37,760
What the fuck!

191
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:39,600
How could you do this shit to me?

192
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:42,720
I fucking love you; you own me the same love.
You’re selfish!

193
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:44,040
June: Love me back, you jerk!
Talay: Stop it!

194
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:49,480
Let's talk later,
when you calm down.

195
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:51,360
No more chats,
I wanted something real.

196
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,200
June: Be with me, now!
Talay: June!

197
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:00,960
I thought my apology was clear.

198
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:38,600
You're a piece of shit!

199
00:28:42,800 --> 00:28:45,280
I'm aware.

200
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:51,680
I'm truly sorry.

201
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:54,720
You don’t need to apologize to me.

202
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:58,680
Apologize to June.

203
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,840
If I could, I would do it.

204
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:08,160
When you had the chance,

205
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:10,360
why didn't you make it right?

206
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:18,160
I did my best, Camp.

207
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:23,960
From what I heard,
I don't think you've done shit.

208
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:27,240
What should I do then?

209
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:30,200
Should I die for her?

210
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:32,120
Should I die for apologizing to her?

211
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:33,240
Give it a try!

212
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:42,240
Dare you?

213
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:53,760
I don't think so.

214
00:30:00,240 --> 00:30:02,320
Did I ask her to die for me?

215
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:20,240
♫Do you know how challenging it is?♫

216
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:28,320
♫Countless millennia, not knowing when we’ll meet similar stars.♫

217
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:34,520
♫Do you know, with just a blink of an eye, just once,♫

218
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:42,200
♫how much the universe and my life can change.♫

219
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:50,440
♫You transform the misty air into the sweet scent of flowers.♫

220
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:58,000
♫You change the silent stars into those from my dreams,♫

221
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:03,080
♫You turn a fleeting second into eternity,♫

222
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:08,360
♫Today, my love for you is the most precious.♫

223
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:12,560
♫Because... it's you.♫

224
00:31:13,160 --> 00:31:17,280
♫We orbit and meet like a dream,♫

225
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:21,800
♫illuminating each other,♫

226
00:31:23,040 --> 00:31:28,800
♫in a universe filled with love.♫

227
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:38,280
♫Do you realize that our meeting isn’t a coincidence?

228
00:31:38,920 --> 00:31:45,040
♫Among the millions, it's you who's caught my glance.♫

229
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:52,280
♫Do you realize the love I have for you♫,

230
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:55,000
♫Is greater than anyone could construe,♫

231
00:31:55,600 --> 00:31:59,160
♫even a universe is too few?♫

232
00:32:12,840 --> 00:32:16,520
You've had feelings for me all this while?

233
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:23,400
Yes, even now.

234
00:32:34,320 --> 00:32:39,520
All those chats,
you knew it was me, didn't you?

235
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:44,520
No, I didn't.

236
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,880
I didn't know it was really you.

237
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,560
I was even too ashamed to meet you.

238
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:59,080
Is that why you didn't tell me about June?

239
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:03,160
Why's it on me?

240
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:08,560
Why did June harm me?

241
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:11,480
Maybe she didn't want us together.

242
00:33:16,360 --> 00:33:19,760
Do you resent me for my actions?

243
00:33:32,840 --> 00:33:34,000
If it was back then,
absolutely.

244
00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:40,640
And even now.

245
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:44,960
But it's more of anger.

246
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:50,960
Remember...

247
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:54,200
I once felt that spark with you too,

248
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:02,240
in the storage room at school.

249
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:06,240
That was the moment.

250
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:16,679
But that was it.

251
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:19,560
Then we never saw each other again.

252
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:26,719
And what about now?

253
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:32,719
I like you, more than before.

254
00:34:37,679 --> 00:34:38,840
I like you.

255
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:46,320
So...

256
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:50,480
can we be more than just friends?

257
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:06,760
Hmm, how about a bath first?

258
00:35:07,640 --> 00:35:08,800
I'm feeling sticky.

259
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:11,520
I want the flashlight this time.

260
00:35:15,040 --> 00:35:17,200
Camp: Oh, I feel so clammy now.
Talay: Alright.

261
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:19,680
I’ll get it for you.

262
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:09,200
Camp, what's going on?

263
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:10,360
Blood!

264
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:51,480
June!

265
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:53,880
You caused my death.

266
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:58,280
Without you,
Talay could've been mine.

267
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:14,560
June, I’m sorry.

268
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:18,520
I’m deeply sorry, June.

269
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:21,080
Please, leave Camp alone.

270
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:22,880
Don’t do anything to him.

271
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:25,440
If you're going to do anything,
do it to me.

272
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:26,880
Please, June!

273
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:29,280
June!

